## Release / Tagging

### Semantic Versioning

```
Format: v{MAJOR}.{MINOR}.{PATCH}

MAJOR: breaking changes (users must change their code / behavior)
MINOR: new features (backward compatible)
PATCH: bug fixes (backward compatible)

Examples:
  v1.0.0  - first stable release
  v1.1.0  - added new feature module
  v1.1.1  - fixed data sort stability bug
  v2.0.0  - redesigned API (breaking changes)
```

### Release Process

1. Merge all features to `main` (or `develop` -> `main`)
2. Update version in package.json / pubspec.yaml / equivalent
3. Update CHANGELOG.md
4. Create git tag: `git tag v1.2.0`
5. Push tag: `git push origin v1.2.0`
6. CI deploys automatically from tag (or manual deploy trigger)

